### --- Per-repo verification override (optional) -----------------------------
# Append `verify=...` to a repo line to override the global VERIFY (set in
# slacker.conf) for THAT repo only. Values: all | none | a comma list of
# gpg,md5,sha. Order with `official` does not matter.
# Use it when one repo ships a broken/missing checksum or signature, so you
# relax only that repo instead of weakening everything. Examples:

#   100  slackware   mirror                                                official  verify=gpg,md5
#   80   conraid     https://slackers.it/repository/slackware64-current              verify=gpg,md5
#   60   alienbob    https://slackware.nl/people/alien/sbrepos/current/x86_64        verify=md5

# ── Source / build-tag priorities ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Packages built from sources that are NOT binary repositories (SlackBuilds.org,
# your own local builds) carry a build tag after the build number, e.g.
# 1_SBo -> _SBo, 1_rtz -> _rtz. Give those tags a priority here, in the same
# scale as the repos above, so upgrade-all treats them as a prioritised source:
# a tagged package is only replaced by a candidate from a repo of HIGHER or
# EQUAL priority. With SBo at 100 below, your SBo packages are never silently
# migrated to conraid/alienbob etc... or downgraded; upgrade them via sbopkg/sbotools/slpkg etc.
# Format:  priority  name   tag

#100        SBo    _SBo
#100        local  _YOURTAG
